E for core loading details. For actions, I’m leaning toward “no_action” unless there’s a good reason for a setup. \\n\\nThe guidance could mention that no global properties are required, but I could clarify test setup if necessary. Perhaps it’s best to stick to built-in properties since there’s no need for YAML unless a module is added. I just need to keep it concise!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Clarifying action guidance**\\n\\nI’m considering whether “no_action” indicates no preparation, though guidance might still include important details. The user is looking for a decision to help with the workflow. I think it could be useful to provide agent guidance suggesting the use of core paths like MapPropertySource or PropsPropertySource, while noting that formats like YAML, JSON, TOML, or HOCON need separate Hoplite modules. That guidance could clarify setup requirements, and it’s important to present that clearly!\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\"action\":\"no_action\",\"summary\":\"hoplite-core is usable and testable without extra setup: its resolved artifact only brings Kotlin/coroutines dependencies transitively, includes built-in properties parsing plus Map/system/env property sources and core decoders, and documentation only requires extra Hoplite modules for non-core formats such as YAML/JSON/TOML/HOCON.\",\"deterministic_setup\":[],\"agent_guidance\":\"No global environment variable or system property is required. Meaningful core-only tests should use MapPropertySource, PropsPropertySource, SystemPropertiesPropertySource with per-test System.setProperty/clearProperty, EnvironmentVariablesPropertySource with an injected map, or .properties/.props resources. Do not use YAML/JSON/TOML/HOCON resources unless a format module is intentionally added, because those parsers are not part of hoplite-core.\",\"risks\":[\"Documentation examples often show YAML configuration, but the docs state non-properties formats require separate hoplite-* parser modules; adding one would broaden scope beyond hoplite-core unless local verification proves it is needed.\"]}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0546b933ca5918b6016a407c0579e8819690a1b5fa5b27ac84\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 3368, "output": 737, "cacheRead": 26624, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 30729, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782610939049, "responseId": "resp_0546b933ca5918b6016a407bfb894481968ac4d2d2ba16f053"}, "toolResults": []}
